cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper discusses solving the classical computer vision problem of bundle adjustment using a graph processor. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper mentions the massively parallel computation and distributed on-chip memory design of graph processors. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper discusses the use of graph processors for AI and mentions the breakthrough performance for message passing algorithms on arbitrary graphs. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the use of Gaussian Belief Propagation for solving bundle adjustment on a graph processor. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper mentions the ability of graph processors to efficiently solve incremental SLAM problems, which are related to graphics and computer vision.
